description:
{"blocks":[{"key":"205ks","text":"This protocol provides step-by-step guidelines to perform the modal analysis of pre-strained hyperelastic rectangular membrane accounting for fluid-structure interactions using Finite Element software ANSYS. The nonlinear constitutive  behavior of the material is modeled by the Mooney-Rivlin equation. The effect of water is considered by the added mass approach. The damping is included as Rayleigh damping. 


","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Hyperelastic material definition using the Mooney-Rivlin formulation from uniaxial test data
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2mhta","text":"Open Engineering Data.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":17}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fdbfc","text":"Ad a new material and define the material name. Verify the units.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4qof","text":"In the Hyperelastic toolbox, choose the Mooney-Rivlin material model with the appropriate number of parameters (double-click on it). Verify that the material constants are correctly inserted.
